showcase-description =
    FreeSynergy Showcase is the living component gallery for the FreeSynergy platform.

    It documents and demonstrates every UI component, design token, layout pattern,
    and interaction behaviour used across the platform — rendered with the currently
    active theme so you see exactly how components look in your environment.

    Primarily useful for developers building FreeSynergy apps or themes, but also
    helpful for understanding the platform's visual language and interaction patterns.

showcase-features =
    - Full component library: buttons, inputs, cards, tables, modals, notifications
    - Design token reference: all CSS custom properties with current values
    - Layout patterns: AppShell, LayoutA/B/C, SplitView, WindowFrame
    - Typography scale and color palette with contrast ratios
    - Live theme preview: all components rendered with the active theme
    - Copy-paste component code examples for Dioxus RSX
    - Icon gallery: all icons in the active icon set with names
